					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/darkstuff" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1581620); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1581620&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183473" alt="DarkStuff" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1581620)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/darkstuff" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1581620); return false;" >DarkStuff</a></span> <span class="odate time_1562600176 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">08 Jul 2019 15:36</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4301220">
									

<p>I think this is an area in which we simply fundamentally disagree with our headcanons. After 133 years of existence, Dr. Wondertainment the company is not giving up, they are realising that they are failing their purpose because they need to be reaching <em>everyone</em>, not just the anomalous community.</p>
<p>The Foundation is giving them the time of day because the Foundation’s purpose is to maintain and preserve normalcy while studying abnormalcy. They are more than willing to push an anomalous company into collapsing back to relative normalcy, especially in exchange for close contact with one of the largest anomalous manufacturers in the world (I’m sure there’s a lot of knowledge to be gained through studying how they make “toys”). That’s where my mind is.</p>
<p>The “real world problems affecting the SCP universe” is personal taste that I can’t get around. There are some ideas I have about that that I will write more so I’ll save them for another time. In any case, I see where you’re coming from, I think we have different views on how certain organisations would act.</p>

							</div>

								
					
